Swiss Not Aware of U.S. Accusation Details, Pictet Tells AZ

-- B y   E l e n a   L o g u t e n k o v a
-- 
2011-11-28T06:50:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-28/swiss-not-aware-of-u-s-accusation-details-pictet-tells-az.html
Swiss banks need to know what the
U.S. is accusing them of to be able to negotiate a solution,
Nicolas Pictet, president of the Swiss private banking
association and a managing partner at Pictet & Cie. told
 Aargauer Zeitung  in an interview.  “Unfortunately we have no clue,” Pictet told the
newspaper. He also said that  UBS AG (UBSN)  and  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN) 
should split off their investment banking units from wealth
management business, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elena Logutenkova in Zurich at 
 elogutenkova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net ; 